Shakespeares Globe On Screen Merry Wives Of Windsor (2010)

Runtime 139 mins. distributed by Kulture Video

Encoded from the original single disc.  There is an act break at 1 hr, 18 mins.

William Belchambers (Abraham Slender) ;
Christopher Benjamin (Sir John Falstaff) ;
Philip Bird (Dr. Caius) ;
Ceri-Lyn Cissone (Anne Page) ;
Serena Evans (Meg Page) ;
Andrew Havill (Frank Ford) ;
Gerard McCarthy (Fenton) 
Sue Wallace (Mistress Quickly) ;
Sarah Woodward (Alice Ford).


Stage director, Christopher Luscombe ;
screen director, Robin Lough.

Summary from container

Shakespeare's hilarious and brilliantly constructed farce delighted audiences at the Globe Theatre in London. Filmed in high definition, the pace, polish, gorgeous Elizabethan costumes and the rollicking performances dazzled the audience.

My notes

   After having seen other versions of Merry Wives Of Windsor I included it in my collection of Globe On Screen for completeness.  But this performance won me over totally and I have enjoyed the number of times I have watched it in total while working on the audio (see paragraph below.)  The story about Merry Wives is that the Queen requested aaplay about Falstaff in love.  Here I have to give immense credit to the whole ensemble cast.  I do not want to give away who gets the biggest cheer at the conclusion of performance,  You will see that for yourself. 


This is my encode with enhanced audio for personal viewing.  It involved balancing the audio so that all voices on stage from different microphones come through at equal volume.  My thanks to videohelp.com for giving the technique and the free software program Levelator 2 which performs the audio balancing.  Levelator is free but no longer in development.

Notes written October 11, 2013
